        "description": {
            "name": "description",
            "type": "java.lang.String",
            "value": "Sometimes, it is necessary to stop executing actions after redirect, but not to stop php engine with exit() or die(). It is required, for instance, by PHPUnit. Currently, there is no such option with Zend_Controller_Action_Helper_Redirector. With setExit(true) it performs exit, with setExit(false) it continues to execute controller actions. The solution is to _forward to some dummy action\/controller after redirect, but I think it would be convinient to have an option to cancel action in redirector API."
        },
